Introduction

Lee Chan, also known for his stage name Dino, is a South Korean dancer, singer, songwriter and composer under Pledis Entertainment. He is the main dancer, sub vocalist, sub rapper and maknae of the boy group SEVENTEEN. He is also a member of the performance sub-unit SVT PERFORMANCE Team

Dino came from a family of dancers. In fact, it was his father that taught him how to dance. After years of training and participating in competitions, Dino became an official Pledis Trainee in 2012. He eventually debuted as the maknae of SEVENTEEN on May 26, 2015 with the mini-album 17 Carat.
